reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality Unit for an affordable price
reviews.reviewText: My Gaming Rig had a top mount for a 200mm fan, so I added this one. I was worried about the noise, but am happy to report this unit is QUIET. It moves plenty of air and keeps things nice and cool while not having any negative downsides. Look no further than this unit. Has a elegant blue led as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet 12V fans with decent airflow
reviews.reviewText: Used in a trailer for the bathroom roof vent. Being 12V, and having it's own shroud, I was able to just drop it in place and use it.Pros: Quiet, works fast enough. Definitely better than the Heng or Camco options. Theirs have the worst blades I've ever seen! We'll see how this one deals with sunlight and heat for a few years, though... Comes with free screws to mount to standard PC cases or heatsinks that accept this size of fan. The larger size is precisely how they're able to stay quiet at that flow rate. Lower RPMs per CFM, you know?Cons: Wish I could get a less quiet version of the same kind at that price, with higher airflow.Oddity: You'll have to splice these with wire nuts and a pair of electrical (cutting) pliers, or order some 3-pin header if you want to go modular. These are intended for interior use (i.e. inside a computer case), so do NOT use where they can get wet or in direct sunlight. Either way, you broke the warranty the moment you used them for this application. At the low price they have compared to 'official' ones of similar quality (not the ones typically installed that are about the same price as this one, we're talking a few times more) for these vents, this is not much of a loss. ;) Avoided the 'RV tax' by using these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars THIS FAN BLOWS......but in a GREAT WAY!
reviews.reviewText: I have the ThermalTake Tower 100 and I love it but I noticed the top was a semi trap for heat. With all the mesh, cables, and everything else the heat just kinda swirled around up there.....SO I bought this fan with the intention to zip tie it to the top panal. had the hopes it would SUCK all the air through the top "mesh" a bit better and it definitely does that. Was worried about the noise......overall its really not NEARLY as bad as I thought it would be. Yes it does put off noise..I mean its a fairly large fan but it's is fairly quiet overall. It's no worse than one of the smaller fans. As it is sitting eye level I wondered if the LEDs would bother me or be a distraction...not at all. They all are either blurred with plastic or facing the other way, but this is not to say that they don't light the area up! A really nice addition to the case and it would be pretty sweet to see ThermalTake consider forming the top around this type of thing to really push the vertical case air situation. Could add a little lip around it make the case 2 inches taller and it would be AMAZING for the air movement!TLDR: Fan really moves air with a nice glow thats not too bright.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Its quiet and it works like it should.
reviews.reviewText: Like the title, it is quiet according to my standards. Although not using it for a PC case (they make cases this big?) they are better for static pressure than high flow airflow. -Which might be better or worse depending on your usage so don't get the idea that you might start making drones out of these lol. I am giving it 4 stars due to how fragile the blades are as I found out when I broke a blade one off when I got a little careless figuring out which way they blow. Luckily enough glue on the broken blade helped balance the fan out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely love this fan
reviews.reviewText: I keep a 200mm fan on the side of my computer to help keep temps down inside. Works great, and lasts almost forever. Second one I bought, first one I accidentally broke a fin off with the power cord. Power cord could be a bit longer, so make sure before you mount it, the connector has the room it needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super quiet, decent air movement, unusual use for it
reviews.reviewText: The condenser fan on my expensive built-in fridge went out, and I needed to get air moving through it to keep stuff cold! The original was 120volt, and discontinued. I used this fan with a cheap plug-in transformer to get it going again. Quieter than the original, and I think the fridge actually runs less with this fan on it. Perfect for my (unusual) use!

reviews.reviewText: Works well. purchased a few of these and on of them created a lot of noise at low and high speeds.The size cools a lot of stuff at low rpm's compared to 140mm or smaller. Will purchase again as needed

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fan. Perfect fit.
reviews.reviewText: Great option for a 200mm budget fan.Only comes in blue led as it states in the package.For the price it's a great fan!If you're skilled enough you can remove the blue led and tinker with other colors. It is tedious work. I really like it though!The white fan next to the Thermaltake is a 140mm Artic fan

Bought this ro cool a Monolith amplifier, I just set it up on top so the air is drawn from the enclosure and it works perfect, keeps the amp as cool as a cucumber, no need to buy specialized contraptions for HI-FI systems at $100+ which are half as efficient. My system is in a separate cubby hole so the noise of the fan is inaudible but even when I'm right over it it's not that noisy. I'm powering it with a cheap 300W computer power supply (there are videos to show you how it will work without being plugged in on a computer ) Very happy with it.
Replaced original case fans that were 8-10 years old and they work flawlessly.

Los uso para extraer aire de mi PC y ayudo a bajar entre 5~10°C la temperatura de los componentes. Su nivel de ruido es casi nulo y los materiales son los adecuados. Quedé satisfecho muy con mi compra.
